article.headline: Furman 73, North Dakota St 61
article.story: GREENVILLE, S.C. (AP) -- Junior forward Robbie Bostain scored a career-high 29 points and hit a pair of 3-pointers during a key second-half rally to lead Furman past North Dakota State 73-61 Saturday afternoon. Bostain sank 8-of-10 field goal attempts including 4-of-5 from 3-point range and made all nine free throws. Two 3-pointers came during a 13-6 run that broke a 46-46 tie and put the Paladins (12-7) ahead to stay. Moussa Diagne added 14 for Furman, which won for the eighth time in its last ten games. Andre Smith and Mike Nelson scored 14 a piece for the Bison (12-10), who forced a 46-46 tie on Lucas Moormann's 15-foot shot with 8:29 remaining. Eric Webb opened Furman's winning run with a 3-point basket at 8:13, and Bostain ended it on a 3-pointer for a 59-52 lead with 5:45 left. Smith had a game-high eight rebounds as the Bison out-rebounded the Paladins 36-25, but Furman shot 51 percent from the field compared to 42 percent for North Dakota State.
